The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Charitable Gilchrist

Mumbai: Australia vice captain Adam Gilchrist will have a date with his sponsored child Mangesh when the world champions take on West Indies at the Brabourne Stadium on Wednesday. Mangesh, a nine-year old slum-dweller, will come to watch the match following a request from the wicketkeeper-batsman himself. Gilchrist also revealed that post-retirement, he is keen on getting involved with charitable works in India. 




